result.text:
I will NEVER be able to comprehend this design change. 

A. They’re almost always wrong.
B. They cost more money (always-on display, need to regenerate upon new products, loss of cold air because they’re always wrong)
C. They do not make the lives of the employees or customers easier (again…displays are always wrong)
D. WTF was wrong with the see-through doors in the first place?

@Walgreens if you wanted to waste money on something, couldn’t you have implemented self-checkout devices instead? Your stores have plenty of real problems that could be solved; there was no need to make up one that didn’t exist.

This pisses me off so bad because like how the fuck was this brainstormed, proposed, and then went through the entire implementation process? I don’t want to shop at a store run by morons I’m sorry I’m afraid I might catch it

result.text:
If you think a $20b company hasn’t had a team empirically analyze the ROI on this, you might be the one missing an elephant in the room!

Marketing is often about displaying the intoxicating platonic ideal of a product. A bottle of Coke is not that interesting or good. The perfect mental image of a Coke is incredible.
